deltaS(i)    = max[ TP(i), TP(i) * (pot * 4/3 - (age-16)/2) ] - max(0,(age-31)*f), where f = 1 for slow, 16 for fast
 If age is in days, define Yd = year2days
 deltaS(i)    = max[ TP(i), TP(i) * (pot * 8 * Yd - 3 * ageDays + 48 Yd)/ (6 Yd)] - max(0,(ageDays-31)*f/Yd)
 If age is in secs, define Ys = year2secs
 deltaS(i)    = max[ TP(i), TP(i) * (pot * 8 * Ys - 3 * ageInSecs + 48 Ys)/ (6 Ys)] - max(0,(ageInSecs-31)*f/Ys)
 skill(i)     = max(0, skill(i) + deltaS(i))
 deltaS(i)    = max[ TP(i), TP(i) * numerator / denominator] - max(0,(ageInSecs-31)*f/Ys)
 skill(i)     = max(0, skill(i) + deltaS(i))

stamina = 0 => do not reduce

throwDice(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: 24 * 3600  / Throws a dice that returns 0 with probability weight0/(weight0+weight1), and 1 otherwise. / So, returning 0 has semantics: "the responsible for weight0 is selected". / We return a uint8, not bool, to allow the return to be used as an idx in an array by the callee. / The formula is derived as follows. Consider a segment which is the union of a segment of length w0, and one of length w1.      0, 1, ... w0-1 | w0 ... w0+w1-1  We want to get a random number in that segment: (w0+w1) * R/(maxR + 1)  w0 wins if (w0+w1) * R/(maxR + 1) < w0 => (w0+w1) * R < w0 * (maxR + 1)  w1 wins otherwise  Limits:  (w0 = 0, w1 != 0) => w0 never wins;   (w0 ! 0, w1 = 0) => w1 never wins;     MAX_RND controls the resolution or fine-graining of the algorithm.
